---
// Sticky FAQ
// ------------
// Description: A sticky FAQ section with a title and a subtitle

// Components
import SectionSticky from '../../blocks/basic/StickySidebar.astro'
import Header from '../../ui/Header.astro'
import DecorationBorder from '../../ui/DecorationBorder.astro'

// Props
type Props = {
title?: string
subtitle?: string
classes?: string
}
const { title = '', subtitle = '', classes = '' } = Astro.props
---

<SectionSticky classes={`${classes ? classes : ''}`}>
<Header
title={title}
subtitle={subtitle}
headingLevel="h2"
titleClasses="bg-white dark:bg-neutral-950 "
slot="sidebar"
/>

<div class="faq">
<div class="faq__item">
<h3 class="faq__item__title">What does a UI/UX design agency actually do?</h3>
<p class="faq__item__text">
We research, design, and test digital experiences — apps, websites, dashboards, and platforms. Our work spans user research, information architecture, wireframing, visual interface design, prototyping, usability testing, and design system creation. We make sure your product looks great and works even better.
</p>
<DecorationBorder type="top bottom" style="dashed" />
</div>
<div class="faq__item">
<h3 class="faq__item__title">How long does a typical UI/UX design project take?</h3>
<p class="faq__item__text">
It depends on scope. A single feature or landing page takes 2–3 weeks. A full product design — including research, wireframes, UI design, and prototyping — typically runs 8–12 weeks. During our discovery call, we'll map out a realistic timeline tailored to your project.
</p>
<DecorationBorder type="top bottom" style="dashed" />
</div>
<div class="faq__item">
<h3 class="faq__item__title">What's the difference between UI and UX design?</h3>
<p class="faq__item__text">
UX (User Experience) design focuses on how a product works — the structure, flows, and logic behind every interaction. UI (User Interface) design focuses on how it looks — typography, colors, spacing, and visual polish. We do both, because a beautiful app that's confusing to use helps no one.
</p>
<DecorationBorder type="top bottom" style="dashed" />
</div>
<div class="faq__item">
<h3 class="faq__item__title">Do you conduct user research before designing?</h3>
<p class="faq__item__text">
Always. Every project starts with understanding your users — through interviews, surveys, analytics review, and competitive analysis. Research-driven design ensures we're solving real problems, not just making assumptions. It's what separates work that looks good from work that actually performs.
</p>
<DecorationBorder type="top bottom" style="dashed" />
</div>
<div class="faq__item">
<h3 class="faq__item__title">Can you redesign our existing product?</h3>
<p class="faq__item__text">
Absolutely — product redesigns are one of our specialties. We begin with a comprehensive UX audit, analyze user behavior data, identify friction points, and then redesign the experience to improve usability, engagement, and conversion. We've helped clients see 40–80% improvements in key metrics through redesigns.
</p>
<DecorationBorder type="top bottom" style="dashed" />
</div>
<div class="faq__item">
<h3 class="faq__item__title">What tools do you use for design?</h3>
<p class="faq__item__text">
Figma is our primary design and prototyping tool — it enables real-time collaboration so your team can follow along. We also use Maze and Hotjar for usability testing, Miro for workshops and journey mapping, and Lottie for micro-animations. All deliverables are shared in formats your developers can work with directly.
</p>
<DecorationBorder type="top bottom" style="dashed" />
</div>
<div class="faq__item">
<h3 class="faq__item__title">Do you build design systems?</h3>
<p class="faq__item__text">
Yes. We create comprehensive design systems with reusable components, design tokens, documentation, and guidelines. A well-built design system ensures visual consistency across your product, speeds up future development, and makes scaling your product significantly easier.
</p>
<DecorationBorder type="top bottom" style="dashed" />
</div>
<div class="faq__item">
<h3 class="faq__item__title">Do you work with startups or only enterprise clients?</h3>
<p class="faq__item__text">
We work with both. We've helped early-stage startups define their MVP and go to market, and we've partnered with enterprise companies on complex platform redesigns. Our flexible engagement models — from focused sprints to ongoing retainers — are designed to fit teams and budgets of all sizes.
</p>
<DecorationBorder type="top bottom" style="dashed" />
</div>
<div class="faq__item">
<h3 class="faq__item__title">How does the design handoff to developers work?</h3>
<p class="faq__item__text">
We provide organized Figma files with annotated specs, exported assets, component documentation, and interaction notes. We don't just throw designs over the wall — we stay available during implementation to answer questions, review builds, and conduct visual QA to ensure the final product matches our designs.
</p>
<DecorationBorder type="top bottom" style="dashed" />
</div>
<div class="faq__item">
<h3 class="faq__item__title">Do you handle front-end development too?</h3>
<p class="faq__item__text">
Our core expertise is UI/UX design, not development. However, we work seamlessly with development teams and can recommend trusted development partners if needed. Our handoff process is designed to minimize back-and-forth and ensure developers can implement designs accurately and efficiently.
</p>
<DecorationBorder type="top bottom" style="dashed" />
</div>
<div class="faq__item">
<h3 class="faq__item__title">How much does a UI/UX design project cost?</h3>
<p class="faq__item__text">
Our plans start at $2,499/month for essential design work and scale based on scope and complexity. We offer transparent pricing with no hidden fees — check our pricing page for detailed plan breakdowns. Every engagement begins with a free discovery call to understand your needs before we propose a plan.
</p>
<DecorationBorder type="top bottom" style="dashed" />
</div>
<div class="faq__item">
<h3 class="faq__item__title">How do we get started?</h3>
<p class="faq__item__text">
Simple — reach out through our contact page or click "Contact Us" in the navigation. We'll schedule a free 30-minute discovery call to learn about your project, understand your goals, and recommend the best approach. From there, we'll send a proposal and kick off as soon as you're ready.
</p>
<DecorationBorder type="top bottom" style="dashed" />
</div>
</div>
</SectionSticky>

<style>
@reference '../../../styles/global.css';
.faq {
@apply flex flex-col gap-6 lg:gap-8;
}
.faq__item {
@apply relative bg-white p-6 lg:p-8 dark:bg-neutral-950;
}
.faq__item__title {
@apply mb-2 text-2xl leading-8;
}
.faq__item__text {
@apply mb-0 text-xl leading-8;
}
</style>
